<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1932,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1932,1957]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[314,399,1932,1956]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[440,494,1933,1956]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[508,593,1932,1956]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[607,712,1933,1957]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[726,797,1932,1956]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[811,1052,1932,1956]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1164,1932,1956]" name="Grenada" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Grenada</collectingCountry>
, and, perhaps, 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1432,1932,1956]" name="Jamaica" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
. Occurs in almost all 
<collectingCountry box="[402,473,1968,1992]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[693,809,1968,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[825,885,1968,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[902,1155,1968,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1171,1259,1968,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Sergipe</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1327,1435,1968,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues, F. H. G. &amp; Silveira, L. &amp; Jacomo, A. T. A. &amp; Carmignotto, A. P. &amp; Bezerra, A. M. R. &amp; Coelho, D. &amp; Garbogini, H. &amp; Pagnozzi, J. &amp; Hass, A." box="[158,404,2004,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" pagination="589 - 600" refId="ref11317" refString="Rodrigues, F. H. G., Silveira, L., Jacomo, A. T. A., Carmignotto, A. P., Bezerra, A. M. R., Coelho, D., Garbogini, H., Pagnozzi, J. &amp; Hass, A. (2002) Composicao e caracterizacao da fauna de mamiferos do Parque Nacional das Emas, Goias. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 19, 589 - 600." type="journal article" year="2002">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis box="[282,331,2004,2028]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Peracchi, A. L. &amp; Lima, I. P. &amp; Reis, N. R. &amp; Nogueira, M. R. &amp; Ortencio-Filho H." box="[416,643,2004,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" pagination="153 - 230" refId="ref11039" refString="Peracchi, A. L., Lima, I. P., Reis, N. R., Nogueira, M. R. &amp; Ortencio-Filho H. (2006) Ordem Chiroptera. In: Reis, N. R., Peracchi, A. L., Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P. (Eds), Mamiferos do Brasil. UEL, Londrina, pp. 153 - 230." type="book chapter" year="2006">
Peracchi 
<emphasis box="[519,569,2004,2028]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Inhabits a variety of habitats such as rainforests, dry forests, and natural and modified open areas, also near to streams. Roost in caves, hollow trees, and buildings (
<bibRefCitation author="Gannon, M. R. &amp; Willig, M. R. &amp; Jones, J. K. Jr." box="[905,1131,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref9743" refString="Gannon, M. R., Willig, M. R. &amp; Jones, J. K. Jr. (1989) Sturnira lilium. Mammalian Species, 333, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1989">
Gannon 
<emphasis box="[1004,1063,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
1989
</bibRefCitation>
). We collected a specimen beside a stream (
<geoCoordinate box="[339,530,223,247]" degrees="13" direction="south" minutes="46" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" precision="1" seconds="35.34" value="-13.776484">13° 46’ 35.34” S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[542,743,223,247]" degrees="46" direction="west" minutes="37" orientation="longitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" precision="1" seconds="32.48" value="-46.625687">46° 37’ 32.48” W</geoCoordinate>
) in São Domingos, GO.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,284]" box="[199,756,259,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,259,284]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" reason="1">Voucher specimen.</emphasis>
One female – CHUNB 1250.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
